ries all over the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2835, \"end\": 2841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9237411596491906, \"rank\": 0.06763380027822828, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2851, \"end\": 2859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.077069370562761e-13, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2891}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Driving home the point, he added, \\\"France, whose culture - and I mean the honoring of the individual, of human rights, of freedom - is grounded very much in Christianity, felt the right thing to do is mock the Christian faith.\\\"\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 3122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9237411596491906, \"rank\": 0.06763380027822828, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3052, \"end\": 3064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9387456045776706, \"rank\": 0.06525132441149563, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9998197750903949, \"rank\": 0.00018025739629322016, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\